standards: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level A: 2.4.4 Link Purpose (In Context)
Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level AAA: 2.4.9 Link Purpose (Link Only)
resultSet.resultTitle: Make sure that link text (and the alternate text for any images that are used as links) describes the destination or purpose of the link.
resultSet.errorDescription: This link is missing its text, but it has a background image. If an link does not have a concise and meaningful text alternative, users who cannot see the image will not understand the purpose of the link, and users of speech-control systems cannot activate the link. If this background image is an icon, the purpose may not be clear to all users, especially those with certain cognitive disabilites. Provide a text alternative with content that clearly and concisely identifies the destination or purpose of the link. If this background image is an icon, consider adding a visible text label as well, perhaps on hover and focus states. If you do not wish to provide visible text, provide the text in a way that is part of the link but hidden from the user (e.g. positioned off-screen, made transparent or very small, etc.).

resultSet.errorTitle: These links have the same text but different destinations.
standards: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level A: 2.4.4 Link Purpose (In Context)
Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level AAA: 2.4.9 Link Purpose (Link Only)
resultSet.resultTitle: Don't reuse the same link text for links that have different destinations
resultSet.errorDescription: This link has the same text as another link that goes to a different place. Using the same text for multiple links which point to different pages is ambiguous and may be confusing for assistive technology users, or for users who have a cognitive disability. Link text should tell the user where they will go if they follow the link. If two links on a page go to two different destinations, use different link text that accurately and concisely describes their destination.

resultSet.errorTitle: These headings are not structured in a hierarchical manner.
standards: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level A: 1.3.1 Info and Relationships
Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level AAA: 2.4.10 Section Headings
resultSet.resultTitle: Make sure that headings are in the right order for the content.
resultSet.errorDescription: The heading structure of this page does not effectively communicate the structure of the content on it. Heading elements provide important benefits: they act as wayfinding cues for in-page navigation, they contribute to page content summaries, and they provide context to the content below them. To do so effectively, headings should follow the `<h1>` to `<h6>` hierarchy and they should not skip levels. Restructure the document's heading order so it uses a clear, ordered, and intuitive hierarchy. Ensure there are no gaps between each numbered heading level and the next.

Opening a new window or new tab unexpectedly can cause confusion for users, particularly for blind users and those with low vision, cogntive impairments or learning disabilities.. Avoid opening links in new windows or tabs. If it is unavoidable, give the user warning via text or a properly marked up and appropriate icon.

focAll.what: Discrepancy between elements that should be and that are Tab-focusable

focInd.what: Focused element displaying no or nostandard focus indicator

link-in-text-block.what: Link is not distinct from surrounding text without reliance on color

styleDiff.what: Heading, link, and button style inconsistencies

e:alt_link_missing.what: Linked image has no text alternative

57.what: Link has no text inside it

91.what: Link has a background image but no text inside it

r17.what: Tab-focusable element is or has an ancestor that is aria-hidden

aria-hidden-focus.what: ARIA hidden element is focusable or contains a focusable element

r53.what: Heading skips one or more levels

heading-order.what: Heading levels do not increase by only one

155.what: Headings are not structured in a hierarchical manner

r57.what: Perceivable text content is not included in any landmark

region.what: Some page content is not contained by landmarks

r64.what: Heading has no non-empty accessible name

r66.what: Text contrast less than AAA requires

color-contrast-enhanced.what: Element has insufficient color contrast (Level AAA)

r69.what: Text outside widget has subminimum contrast

r73.what: Paragraph of text has insufficient line height

r78.what: No content between two headings of the same level

r83.what: Overflow is hidden or clipped if the text is enlarged

r87.what: First focusable element is not a link to the main content

aria-allowed-attr.what: ARIA attribute is invalid for the role of its element

frame-tested.what: Some content is in an iframe and therefore may not be testable for accessibility

hidden-content.what: Some content is hidden and therefore may not be testable for accessibility

identical-links-same-purpose.what: Links with the same accessible name may serve dissimilar purposes

a:alt_duplicate.what: Two images near each other have the same text alternative

a:link_redundant.what: Adjacent links go to the same URL

a:title_redundant.what: Title attribute text is the same as text or alternative text

79.what: Link has a title attribute that is the same as the text inside the link

73.what: Link text is too generic to communicate the purpose or destination

98.what: Links have the same text but different destinations

144.what: Line height is insufficent to properly display the computed font size

152.what: Actionable element is smaller than the minimum required size

153.what: Long string of text is in all caps

218.what: Link opens in a new window without user control
